<div class="mdui-typo"><h1 id="debt-n">debt <strong><em>n</em></strong></h1>
<p>英 /det/    美 /det/  </p>
<h2 id="_1">释义</h2>
<h4 id="1-c-u">1.★ <strong>[C] &amp; [U] 债务；欠债；人情债：</strong></h4>
<div class="mdui-typo"><blockquote><p>They will send kids to college whatever it takes, even if that means a huge amount of debts.
他们将不惜一切代价送孩子上大学，即使这会使他们债台高筑。</p><footer>2011 山东</footer></div>

<h2 id="_2">固定搭配</h2>
<h3 id="fall-get-run-into-debt">fall / get / run into debt</h3>
<p>1.<strong>借债；负债：</strong>  </p>
<div class="mdui-typo"><blockquote><p>It's much easier to get into debt than to get out of debt.
借债容易还债难。</p></div>

<h3 id="in-debt-to-sb">in debt (to sb)</h3>
<p>1.<strong>欠 (某人) 债；受 (某人) 恩惠：</strong>  </p>
<div class="mdui-typo"><blockquote><p>Nearly half the college students said they were in debt.
近一半的大学生说自己欠债。</p></div>

<div class="mdui-typo"><blockquote><p>I’m in debt to him for his help. 
对于他的帮助，我欠他一份人情。</p></div>

<h3 id="out-of-debt">out of debt</h3>
<p>1.<strong>不欠债</strong>  </p>
<h3 id="pay-off-ones-debts">pay off one’s debts</h3>
<p>1.<strong>还清债务</strong>  </p></div>